## Before shutting down the old server

1. [MA-003] Recreate active cron job — Recreate this cron job on the destination adapting the /home/<user> paths to the new account.

## Post-cutover checks

1. Load every site over HTTPS and confirm the homepage renders from the destination.
2. Send and receive a test message for at least one mailbox per domain.
3. Run AutoSSL on the destination and confirm every domain serves a valid certificate.
4. Verify public DNS resolves every domain to the destination server once TTLs expire.
5. Confirm recreated cron jobs actually ran (check their output/log once).

